SIMPLE: wimble
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wimble
<hw>Wim"ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>wimbil</ets>; akin to Dan. <ets>vimmel</ets>, OD.
<ets>wemelen</ets> to bore. Cf. <er>Gimlet</er>.]</ety> <def>An
instrument for boring holes, turned by a handle.</def> Specifically:
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A gimlet.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧ It is but like the little
<xex>wimble</xex>, to let in the greater auger.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Selden.</au>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A stonecutter's brace for boring holes in stone.</def>
<sd>(c)</sd> <def>An auger used for boring in earth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wimble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wimble
<hw>Wim"ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Wimbled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Wimbling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To bore or pierce,
as with a wimble.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A foot soldier . . . <xex>wimbled</xex>
also a hole through said coffin.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Wood.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wimble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Wimble
<hw>Wim"ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Sw.
<ets>vimmel</ets>kantig giddy, whimsical, dial. Sw. <ets>vimmla</ets> to
be giddy or skittish, and E. <ets>whim</ets>.]</ety> <def>Active;
nimble.</def><mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

